'''美国诉温莎案'''（{{lang|en|''United States v. Windsor''}}）， {{scite|570|12|2013}}，是[[美国最高法院|美国最高法院]]有关[[美国同性婚姻|美国同性婚姻]]的重要案件，该案是对[[美国纽约南区地方法院|美国纽约南区地方法院]]一审，[[美国联邦第二巡回上诉法院|美国联邦第二巡回上诉法院]]二审维持原判的[[艾迪絲·溫莎|艾迪絲·溫莎]]诉美利坚合众国案进行审查，在该案中，两审法院均认定《[[捍卫婚姻法案|捍卫婚姻法案]]》第3章中将“婚姻”定义为“一名男性和一名女性之间成为夫妻的法律结合”，将“配偶”定义为“异性的夫或妻”的规定违宪。美国最高法院于2012年12月接受了上诉，并于2013年3月27日听取了口头辩论。2013年6月26日，联邦最高法院裁定温莎胜诉，认定《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章[[违宪|违宪]]。<ref name=''Opinion''>{{cite web |url=http://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/12pdf/12-307_g2bh.pdf |title=UNITED STATES v. WINDSOR, XECUTOR OF THE ESTATE OF SPYER, ET AL. CERTIORARI TO THE UNITED STATES COURT OF APPEALS FOR THE SECOND CIRCUIT |publisher=supremecourt.gov |date=June 26, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20130627013713/http://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/12pdf/12-307_g2bh.pdf |archivedate=2013年6月27日 }}</ref>各州的最高法院此後開始以此為基礎通過公民團體製造的案件，裁定該州禁止同性婚姻的法律違憲。這裁決亦為為[[奧貝格費爾訴霍奇斯案|奧貝格費爾訴霍奇斯案]]（英語：Obergefell v. Hodges，2015年）使[[美國同性婚姻|美國同性婚姻]]全國合法化打下基礎。

== 背景 ==
2007年，纽约州居民'''伊迪丝·温莎'''和'''西娅·斯派尔'''在40年相伴后，在[[加拿大|加拿大]][[安大略省|安大略省]][[多伦多|多伦多]]结婚。双方都是女性。<ref>{{cite news |last=Shapiro |first=Lila |title=Edie Windsor vs. DOMA: 83-Year-Old Lesbian Petitions U.S. Supreme Court To Hear Case |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/07/16/edie-windsor-doma_n_1675983.html |accessdate=July 30, 2012 |newspaper=[[哈芬登郵報|The Huffington Post]] |date=July 16, 2012}}</ref>加拿大首位公开承认同性恋取向的法官哈维·布朗斯通主持了婚礼。<ref>{{cite news|title=Thea Spyer and Edith Windsor|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/05/27/fashion/weddings/27spyer.html|accessdate=January 1, 2013|newspaper=[[紐約時報|The New York Times]]|date=May 27, 2007}}</ref>2009年，斯派尔过世，此时纽约州也已承认在其他司法管辖区中结成的同性婚姻。<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[美國公民自由聯盟|American Civil Liberties Union]] |url=http://www.aclu.org/lgbt-rights/windsor-v-united-states-thea-edie-doma |title=''Windsor v. United States'': Edie Windsor Challenges DOMA |date=February 23, 2011 |accessdate=February 28, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |publisher=Law.com |url=http://www.law.com/jsp/nylj/PubArticleNY.jsp?id=1202483113125& |first=Mark |last=Hamblett |title=Obama No Longer Will Defend Marriage Act |date=February 24, 2011 |accessdate=February 28, 2011}}</ref>在斯派尔死后，继承其妻房产的温莎被要求支付超过363,000美元的联邦遗产税。而同样情况下如果是一对异性恋夫妻，则可以获得无最高限额的配偶税收减免，而不必支付任何联邦遗产税。<ref>{{cite news |last=Schwartz |first=John |title=Gay Couple to Sue over U.S. Marriage Law |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/11/09/us/09marriage.html |accessdate=July 16, 2012 |newspaper=[[纽约时报|The New York Times]] |date=November 8, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Johnson |first=Chris |title=Two New Lawsuits Target DOMA |url=http://www.washingtonblade.com/2010/11/09/two-new-lawsuits-target-doma/ |accessdate=July 16, 2012 |newspaper=Washington Blade|date=November 9, 2010}}</ref>而由于不享受配偶税收减免的优待，温莎从斯派尔那里继承来的财产只有350万美元的免税额，超过部分则要支付联邦遗产税。<ref>http://wills.about.com/od/understandingestatetaxes/a/estatetaxchart.htm</ref>

温莎咨询了宝维斯国际律师事务所（Paul, Weiss, Rifkind, Wharton & Garrison LLP）合伙人罗伯塔·卡普兰（Roberta Kaplan）的意见，后者之前曾在2006年代理过一个上诉至联邦上诉法庭、有关纽约州同性伴侣无法成婚的案件。在[[美国公民自由联盟|美国公民自由联盟]]的合作下，凯普兰同意接受此案。<ref>{{cite news|author = Applebome, Peter |title=Reveling in Her Supreme Court Moment|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/11/nyregion/edith-windsor-gay-widow-revels-in-supreme-court-fight.html|accessdate=December 13, 2012|newspaper=The New York Times|date=December 10, 2012}}</ref>

=== 地方法院 ===
宝维斯国际律师事务所同美国公民自由联盟代表作为斯派尔遗产执行人的温莎，向纽约南区地方法院提起诉讼。<ref>[http://www.aclu.org/lgbt-rights/windsor-v-united-states-complaint ''Windsor v. United States'', Complaint]. Retrieved March 1, 2011.</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Widow's $363,000 Tax Bill Led to Obama Shift on Marriage Act |first=Andrew M. |last=Harris |url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-02-28/widow-s-363-000-tax-bill-led-to-obama-shift-on-marriage-act.html |work =Bloomberg Businessweek |date=February 28, 2011 |accessdate=March 5, 2011}}</ref>

2011年2月23日，司法部长[[埃里克·霍尔德|埃里克·霍尔德]]就温莎案、{{link-en|佩德森诉人事管理委员会案|Pedersen v. Office of Personnel Management}}挑战《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章一事发表声明。声明中表示：奥巴马政府认为根据[[性取向|性取向]]对人进行区分的做法应该适用较严格审查标准（heightened scrutiny），因此无法继续为《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章的合宪性辩护。<ref name="HolderPressRelease">{{cite press release |url=http://www.justice.gov/opa/pr/2011/February/11-ag-222.html |title=Statement of the Attorney General on Litigation Involving the Defense of Marriage Act |date=February 23, 2011 |accessdate=February 23, 2011 |publisher=[[美國司法部|United States Department of Justice]]}}</ref>在国会废止该法案或者被法院宣布为违宪前，行政部门会继续执行该法案。<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Gay & Lesbian Advocates & Defenders (GLAD) |url=http://www.glad.org/current/news-detail/glad-statement-on-dojs-announcement-it-wont-defend-constitutionality-of-dom/ |title=GLAD Statement on DOJ's Announcement It Won't Defend Constitutionality of DOMA in ''Pedersen'' |date=February 23, 2011 |accessdate=February 23, 2011 |archive-date=2011-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110227090354/http://www.glad.org/current/news-detail/glad-statement-on-dojs-announcement-it-wont-defend-constitutionality-of-dom |dead-url=yes }}</ref>4月18日，{{link-en|保罗·克莱门特|Paul Clement}}代表[[美国众议院|美国众议院]]{{link-en|两党法律顾问小组|Bipartisan Legal Advisory Group}}（BLAG）提交动议，要求允许他们干预此案件，“仅旨在为《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章的合宪性进行辩护”。[[美国司法部|美国司法部]]的律师并未反对该动议。<ref>{{cite web |work=Metro Weekly |url=http://www.Metroweekly.com/poliglot/2011/04/house-leadership-seeks-to-inte.html |first=Chris |last=Geidner |title=House Leadership Seeks to Intervene in DOMA Case |date=April 18, 2011 |accessdate=April 19, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110425041913/http://www.metroweekly.com/poliglot/2011/04/house-leadership-seeks-to-inte.html |archivedate=2011年4月25日 }}</ref>

温莎的律师团提交动议，要求在6月24日进行[[简易判决|简易判决]]。<ref>{{cite web |work={{link-en|地鐵周刊|Metro Weekly|Metro Weekly}} |url=http://Metroweekly.com/poliglot/MotionSJ.pdf |title=Memorandum in Support of Plaintiff's Motion for Summary Judgment |date=June 24, 2011 |accessdate=August 3, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003123603/http://metroweekly.com/poliglot/MotionSJ.pdf |archivedate=2011年10月3日 }}</ref>7月16日，纽约州总检察长{{link-en|埃里克·施奈德曼|Eric Schneiderman}}提交了一份辩护状，支持温莎的诉请，认为《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章无法通过严格审查标准，构成了“国家权力对于婚姻定义的粗暴干涉”。<ref>{{cite web |work={{link-en|地鐵周刊|Metro Weekly|Metro Weekly}} |url=http://Metroweekly.com/poliglot/2011/07/new-york-attorney-general-take.html |first=Chris |last=Geidner |title=New York Attorney General Takes Edith Windsor's Side in DOMA Challenge |date=July 26, 2011 |accessdate=July 26, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110806181726/http://www.metroweekly.com/poliglot/2011/07/new-york-attorney-general-take.html |archivedate=2011年8月6日 }}</ref>8月1日，两党法律顾问小组提交的辩护状则反对温莎有关简易判决的动议，认为对于性取向不应适用较严格的审查标准。<ref>{{cite web |work=Metro Weekly |url=http://Metroweekly.com/poliglot/2011/08/house-gop-leaders-say-court-sh.html |first=Chris |last=Geidner |title=House GOP Leaders Say Court Should Dismiss Edith Windsor's Lawsuit, Find DOMA Constitutional |date=August 2, 2011 |accessdate=August 2, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110806181651/http://www.metroweekly.com/poliglot/2011/08/house-gop-leaders-say-court-sh.html |archivedate=2011年8月6日 }}</ref>

2012年6月6日，法官{{link-en|芭芭拉·S·琼斯|Barbara S. Jones}}做出判决，根据合理审查标准（rational basis review），《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章违背了[[美國憲法第五修正案|第五修正案]]平等保护的承诺，侵犯了原告方的权利，认定违宪，裁定温莎获得退税补偿。<ref>[http://lawprofessors.typepad.com/files/windsor_doma.pdf ''Windsor v. United States''], 833 F. Supp. 2d 394 (S.D.N.Y 2012).</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Katz|first=Basil|title=Defense of Marriage Act Unconstitutional: Judge|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/06/us-usa-gaymarriage-idUSBRE8551JW20120606|publisher=[[路透社|Reuters]]|accessdate=December 10, 2012|date=6 June 6, 2012}}</ref>

=== 上诉法院 ===
尽管赞同该判决，但为配合两党法律顾问小组要为该法案辩护的要求，美国司法部仍于2012年6月14日遞交上诉状。<ref>{{cite web |work=Metro Weekly |url=http://www.Metroweekly.com/poliglot/2012/06/domas-federal-definition-of-marriage-what-is-happe.html |first=Chris |last=Geidner |title=The DOMA Lawsuits: What Is Happening? |date=June 18, 2012 |accessdate=June 19, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120621041600/http://www.metroweekly.com/poliglot/2012/06/domas-federal-definition-of-marriage-what-is-happe.html |archivedate=2012年6月21日 }}</ref>7月19日，两党法律顾问小组提交动议，认为由于其在地方法院中对此案的立场，要求将司法部排除在第二巡回法院上诉案之外。<ref>{{cite web |title=Windsor v. USA – BLAG moves to dismiss DOJ appeal |url=http://www.prop8trialtracker.com/qh/windsor-v-usa-blag-moves-to-dismiss-doj-appeal/ |publisher=Prop 8 Trial Tracker |accessdate=July 24, 2012 }}{{dead link|date=2018年4月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>温莎的律师团则于2012年7月16日向最高法院提交決前受理的請願書，希望最高法院考虑到原告方年事已高、身体状况不佳，不必等待第二巡回法院的审查就直接由最高法院判决。<ref>{{cite web |work={{link-en|地鐵周刊|Metro Weekly|Metro Weekly}} |url=http://www.Metroweekly.com/poliglot/2012/07/widow-petitions-doma-case-to-the-supreme-court.html |first=Justin |last=Snow |title=Widow Petitions DOMA Case to the Supreme Court |date=July 16, 2012 |accessdate=July 16, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722133026/http://www.metroweekly.com/poliglot/2012/07/widow-petitions-doma-case-to-the-supreme-court.html |archivedate=2012年7月22日 }}</ref>尽管如此，第二巡回法院仍然在8月3日宣布将于9月27日开始口头辩论。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.prop8trialtracker.com/qh/windsor-v-usa-2nd-circuit-oral-arguments-set-for-september-27/ |title=Windsor v. USA: 2nd Circuit oral arguments set for September 27 |publisher=Prop 8 Trial Tracker |date=August 3, 2012 }}{{dead link|date=2018年4月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

9月27日，审判长丹尼斯·贾可布和法官切斯特·J·斯特劳勃以及克里斯托弗·F·卓尼听取了该案的辩论。<ref>{{cite news |last=Johnson |first=Chris |title=GOP att'y strongly defends DOMA in N.Y. widow's lawsuit |url=http://www.washingtonblade.com/2012/09/27/gop-atty-strongly-defends-doma-in-n-y-widows-lawsuit/ |accessdate=September 28, 2012 |newspaper= Washington Blade |date=September 27, 2012}}</ref>10月18日，第二巡回上诉法院维持了地方法院有关《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章违宪的判决。<ref name="Reuters20121018">{{cite news |last=Baynes |first=Terry |title=Appeals court rules against Defense of Marriage Act |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/18/us-usa-gaymarriage-appeal-idUSBRE89H12L20121018|accessdate=October 18, 2012 |publisher= [[路透社|Reuters]] |date=October 18, 2012}}</ref><ref>''[http://www.ca2.uscourts.gov/decisions/isysquery/436f323b-5e40-411a-9026-98fa59ffb645/1/doc/12-2335_complete_opn.pdf Windsor v. United States]'', 699 F.3d 169 (2d Cir. 2012).</ref>法官的多数意见中写道：很容易看出，对同性恋的歧视由来已久。因此他们属于“准可疑分类”，对于任何试图限制其权利的法律都应适用较严格的审查标准。審判長賈可布寫到，因为《捍卫婚姻法案》无法通过审查，因此它违反宪法第五修正案有关平等保护的规定，裁定违宪。<ref name="Reuters20121018" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Schwartz |first=John |title=U.S. Marriage Act Is Unfair to Gays, Court Panel Says |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/10/19/us/appeals-court-rules-against-defense-of-marriage-act.html |accessdate= December 13, 2012 |newspaper= The New York Times |date= October 18, 2012}}</ref>

=== 最高法院 ===
2012年9月11日，在温莎一方提交決前受理请愿后、上诉法院判决前，美国司法部也向最高法院提交了決前受理请愿。<ref>[http://www.scribd.com/doc/105738696/12-307-1-DOJ-Petition Petition for Certiorari (No 12-307).] Retrieved December 8, 2012.</ref>在10月18日上诉法院判决后，各方又提交了补充辩护状。<ref name="docket 12-307">[http://www.supremecourt.gov/Search.aspx?FileName=/docketfiles/12-307.htm Docket report for ''United States v. Windsor'' (12-307)]. Retrieved December 7, 2012.</ref>

12月7日，最高法院受理了该案（此时已是美国诉温莎案），接受了司法部的请愿。除了司法部提出的有关《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章是否违反宪法第五修正案中所承诺的对于同性伴侣的同等保护这一问题外，法院还要求各方针对另外两个问题展开辩论：政府一方对于第二巡回法院决定的支持是否让最高法院对该案无管辖权，以及两党法律顾问小组根据[[美利坚合众国宪法第三条|美国宪法第三条]]的规定，两党法律顾问小组在该案中是否有参加权。<ref>{{cite web |title=Order List |url=http://www.supremecourt.gov/orders/courtorders/120712zr_3f14.pdf|publisher=United States Supreme Court|accessdate=December 8, 2012|date=December 7, 2012}}</ref>

12月28日，两党法律顾问小组提交了自己的上诉请愿，<ref group=n>Docket No. [http://www.supremecourt.gov/Search.aspx?FileName=/docketfiles/12-785.htm 12-785]</ref>让最高法院在认定司法部对于第二巡回法院判决的赞同使得该院无管辖权后，仍可对《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章的合宪性进行审查。<ref>{{cite news |last=Geidner |first=Chris |title=House Republican Leaders Want This To Be The Last Fight Over DOMA |url=http://www.buzzfeed.com/chrisgeidner/house-republicans-want-this-to-be-the-last-fight-o |accessdate=January 2, 2013 |publisher = {{link-en|巴茲飼料網|BuzzFeed|BuzzFeed}} |date=January 2, 2013}}</ref>最高法院于2013年3月27日听取了口头辩论。<ref>{{cite web|title=United States, Petitioner v. Edith Schlain Windsor, in Her Capacity as Executor of the Estate of Thea Clara Spyer, et al.|url=http://www.supremecourt.gov/Search.aspx?FileName=/docketfiles/12-307.htm|work=Docket|publisher=[[美國最高法院|Supreme Court of the United States]]|accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref>

== 判决 ==
=== 多数意见 ===
2013年6月26日，美国最高法院以5-4的结果认定《捍卫婚姻法案》第3章违宪，“是对于第五修正案中保护个人平等自由的背离”。<ref name="Opinion">{{cite web |url=http://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/12pdf/12-307_g2bh.pdf | title =United States v. Windsor |author=''[[美國最高法院|Supreme Court of the United States]]'' |publisher=supremecourt.gov |date=June 26, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627013713/http://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/12pdf/12-307_g2bh.pdf |archivedate =2013年6月27日 }}</ref>[[美国最高法院大法官|大法官]][[安东尼·肯尼迪|安东尼·肯尼迪]]起草了多数意见，联名的有大法官[[鲁思·金斯伯格|金斯伯格]]、[[史蒂芬·布雷耶|布雷耶]]、[[索尼娅·索托马约尔|索托马约尔]]以及[[艾蕾娜·卡根|卡根]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/supreme-court/2013/06/26/f0039814-d9ab-11e2-a016-92547bf094cc_story.html |title=Supreme Court strikes down Defense of Marriage Act |publisher=washingtonpost.com |author=Robert Barnes |date =June 26, 2013}}</ref>最高法院这样写道：  

{{quote box
|《捍卫婚姻法案》的主要作用是在州认可的婚姻中区分出了一个子集，并使其受到不平等待遇。其主要目的是推行不平等，而不是其他诸如政府效率的原因。……<br/><br/>《捍卫婚姻法案》破坏了州认可的同性婚姻对于公众和个人的重大意义；因为它是在告诉这些情侣们以及全世界，他们原本有效的婚姻并不受到联邦承认。这就让同性伴侣们处于次等婚姻的不稳定状态。这种区分贬低了同性伴侣，他们的道德和性选择本是受到宪法保护的，参见劳伦斯案（539 U. S. 558），他们的伴侣关系也是联邦希望给予尊严的。它还羞辱了成千上万名目前由同性伴侣抚养的儿童。受质疑的法律让这些儿童更加难以理解自己所在家庭的完整性和亲密性，以及其同所在社区和日常生活中其他家庭的和睦性。<br/><br/>《捍卫婚姻法案》下，同性婚姻伴侣因为政府的法令，而以可见且公开地方式承担起生活之重负。<br/>
……
<br/>这一联邦立法是无效的，因为联邦制定婚姻法律本应寻求保护人格和尊严，但是这一法案却贬低并伤害了他们。由于意图取代这种保护，区别对待同性婚姻者，此项联邦立法违反了第五修正案。<ref group=n>原文：DOMA's principal effect is to identify a subset of state-sanctioned marriages and make them unequal. The principal purpose is to impose inequality, not for other reasons like governmental efficiency. ...
<br/><br/>
DOMA undermines both the public and private significance of state-sanctioned same-sex marriages; for it tells those couples, and all the world, that their otherwise valid marriages are unworthy of federal recognition. This places same-sex couples in an unstable position of being in a second-tier marriage. The differentiation demeans the couple, whose moral and sexual choices the Constitution protects, see Lawrence, 539 U. S. 558, and whose relationship the State has sought to dignify. And it humiliates tens of thousands of children now being raised by same-sex couples. The law in question makes it even more difficult for the children to understand the integrity and closeness of their own family and its concord with other families in their community and in their daily lives.
<br/><br/>
Under DOMA, same-sex married couples have their lives burdened, by reason of government decree, in visible and public ways.
<br/>
...
<br/>
The federal statute is invalid, for no legitimate purpose overcomes the purpose and effect to disparage and to injure those whom the State, by its marriage laws, sought to protect in personhood and dignity. By seeking to displace this protection and treating those persons as living in marriages less respected than others, the federal statute is in violation of the Fifth Amendment.</ref><ref>http://www.huffingtonpost.com/scottie-thomaston/analysis-supreme-court-in_b_3506136.html</ref>
|align = left
|style = font-size: 100%;
}}
